Uses of Package
popt4jlib

  • Packages that use popt4jlib 
    Package Description
    analysis
    analysis package: a package implementing parallel algorithms for numerical differentiation and integration, and also including more complex transformations such as convolution.
    graph.packing
    Optimization package that obtains near-optimal solution to the 1- and 2-packing combinatorial optimization problem.
    graph.partitioning
    Package defines interfaces and implements algorithms for graph and hyper-graph partitioning.
    parallel
    parallel package: an implementation of all the synchronization, communication & coordination primitives required in popt4jlib.
    parallel.distributed
    Extends the basic functionality found in the parallel package over many remote JVMs distributed over a network of machines.
    popt4jlib
    popt4jlib: a parallel optimization library for Java.
    popt4jlib.BH
    Generalized Adaptive Basin Hopping
    popt4jlib.DE
    Differential Evolution Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.EA
    Evolutionary Algorithms Parallel Implementation
    popt4jlib.GA
    Genetic Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.GradientDescent
    Gradient-Descent Type Algorithms Parallel Implementation (suitable for real vector function optimization).
    popt4jlib.GradientDescent.stochastic
    Stochastic Gradient-Descent Type Algorithms Parallel Implementation (suitable for (deterministic or stochastic) real vector function optimization).
    popt4jlib.LIP
    package contains parallel implementations of some well-known algorithms for Linear Integer Programming, including Balas' Additive Algorithm (dating back to an Operations Research article of 1965).
    popt4jlib.LocalSearch
    Local Search algorithms parallel implementation for combinatorial optimization problems.
    popt4jlib.MSSC
    Package implements algorithms for Minimum-Sum-of-Square(-Errors)-Clustering, a well-defined optimization problem.
    popt4jlib.MinExplainSet
    Package implements algorithms for the so-called Minimum Explaining Set, an optimization problem arising in Data Mining applications.
    popt4jlib.MonteCarlo
    Monte-Carlo Search Parallel Implementation (aka random search)
    popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning
    Package defines parallel/distributed versions of well-known Number Partitioning algorithms.
    popt4jlib.PS
    Particle Swarm Optimization Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.PS.FA
    Firefly Algorithm Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.SA
    Simulated Annealing Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.network
    Network Flow Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.neural
    Neural Network Related Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    popt4jlib.neural.costfunction
    Cost Functions for Neural Network Related Algorithms Parallel Implementation.
    tests
    tests package: defines functions used for testing the optimization algorithms in the popt4jlib library.
    tests.sic.rnqt.nbin
    tests.sic.rnqt.nbin package: implements exact and/or heuristic algorithms for the global optimization of long-run expected average costs of a single-echelon inventory control system operating a periodic review control policy (R,nQ,T) facing stochastic demands that are distributed according to the Negative Binomial distribution (a compound Poisson distribution where customers arrive at intervals that are spaced according to the Poisson distribution, but their order quantities are logarithmically distributed instead of being always single unit demands) in a continuous time cost-accounting setting.
    tests.sic.rnqt.norm
    tests.sic.rnqt.norm package: implements exact and/or heuristic algorithms for the global optimization of long-run expected average costs of a single-echelon inventory control system operating a periodic review control policy (R,nQ,T) facing normally distributed demands in a continuous time cost-accounting setting.
    tests.sic.rnqt.poisson
    tests.sic.rnqt.poisson package: implements exact and/or heuristic algorithms for the global optimization of long-run expected average costs of a single-echelon inventory control system operating a periodic review control policy (R,nQ,T) facing Poisson distributed demands in a continuous time cost-accounting setting.
    tests.sic.sST.det
    tests.sic.sST.det package: implements exact and/or heuristic algorithms for the global optimization of long-run exact average costs of a single-echelon inventory control system operating a periodic review control policy (R,nQ,T) facing deterministic demands with constant demand rate, in a continuous time cost-accounting setting.
    tests.sic.sST.poisson
    tests.sic.sST.poisson package: implements exact and/or heuristic algorithms for the global optimization of long-run expected average costs of a single-echelon inventory control system operating a periodic review control policy (s,S,T) facing Poisson distributed demands in a continuous time cost-accounting setting.
  • Classes in popt4jlib used by analysis 
    Class and Description
    FunctionIntf
    interface defining a function mapping objects of some domain (not necessarily R^n) to R.
    VecFunctionIntf
    definition of a vector function mapping vectors in R^n to vectors in R^m.
    VectorIntf
    defines vectors in R^n.
  • Classes in popt4jlib used by graph.packing 
    Class and Description
    AllChromosomeMakerClonableIntf
    interface specifying that AllChromosomeMakerIntf objects can be cloned.
    AllChromosomeMakerIntf
    allows the definition of the neighborhood of a point in a search space that is needed by Local-Search algorithms in combinatorial optimization problems.
    BoolVector
    represents a vector of booleans (alternative to BitSet, or Set<Long> that in fact may hold bit-sets of arbitrarily large size).
    FunctionIntf
    interface defining a function mapping objects of some domain (not necessarily R^n) to R.
    IntArray1SparseVector
    sparse int[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
    ObserverIntf
    This interface allows objects that want to be "monitoring" other "Subject" objects to be notified whenever a change in the subject occurs, and act accordingly.
    OptimizerException
    Exception class used by most optimization algorithms in the popt4jlib package to indicate abnormal execution of some task.
    SubjectIntf
    The SubjectIntf implements the Subject Object's methods in the well-known Observer Design Pattern.

  • Classes in popt4jlib used by popt4jlib 
    Class and Description
    AllChromosomeMakerClonableIntf
    interface specifying that AllChromosomeMakerIntf objects can be cloned.
    AllChromosomeMakerIntf
    allows the definition of the neighborhood of a point in a search space that is needed by Local-Search algorithms in combinatorial optimization problems.
    Arg2ChromosomeMakerIntf
    interface defining the methods that an object must support so as to be able to convert a function argument (an object type that the function being minimized accepts) into a chromosome object (notion used in GA, SA, PS, EA meta-heuristics among others).
    BoolVector
    represents a vector of booleans (alternative to BitSet, or Set<Long> that in fact may hold bit-sets of arbitrarily large size).
    BoolVector.BVAux
    auxiliary nested class, not part of the public API.
    BoolVector.BVThread
    auxiliary nested class not part of the public API.
    Chromosome2ArgMakerIntf
    the inverse map of the Arg2ChromosomeMakerIntf.
    DblArray1SparseVector
    sparse double[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
    DblArray1SparseVectorMT
    sparse double[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
    DblArray1Vector
    double[] implementation of VectorIntf.
    DblArray1VectorPool
    implements a thread-local pool of DblArray1Vector objects.
    DblArray2SparseMatrix
    sparse 2-D matrix class containing doubles.
    FunctionBase
    The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that keeps track of how many times a function has been evaluated.
    FunctionEvaluationTask
    auxiliary class used when the user requests function evaluations to be executed in separate threads in a thread-pool for a limited time so as to avoid "locking-up" the minimization process by function evaluations that take too long to complete (such evaluations are "lost" by the minimization process even if they eventually complete).
    FunctionIntf
    interface defining a function mapping objects of some domain (not necessarily R^n) to R.
    ImmigrationIslandOpIntf
    interface that may be used in island models of population-based optimization meta-heuristics, allowing for the customization of the island migration topologies.
    IntArray1SparseVector
    sparse int[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
    IntArray2SparseMatrix
    sparse 2-D matrix class containing integers.
    LocalOptimizerIntf
    interface for local-optimization methods (methods seeking a local minimum in the neighborhood of a "starting point" solution).
    ObserverIntf
    This interface allows objects that want to be "monitoring" other "Subject" objects to be notified whenever a change in the subject occurs, and act accordingly.
    OptimizerException
    Exception class used by most optimization algorithms in the popt4jlib package to indicate abnormal execution of some task.
    OptimizerIntf
    the interface every optimizer (for unconstrained optimization) must implement.
    PoolableObjectIntf
    interface specifies the contract for objects that can participate in thread-local object pools.
    RandomArgMakerClonableIntf
    interface specifying that RandomArgMakerIntf objects can be cloned.
    RandomArgMakerIntf
    interface class for constructing random arguments for a function.
    SparseVectorIntf
    this interface extends the standard VectorIntf in that it provides two methods to allow for (fast) loops over the non-zero (non-default-valued more generally) elements of a sparse vector.
    SubjectIntf
    The SubjectIntf implements the Subject Object's methods in the well-known Observer Design Pattern.
    VecFunctionIntf
    definition of a vector function mapping vectors in R^n to vectors in R^m.
    VectorIntf
    defines vectors in R^n.
